snippet.textDisplay: Hey Adam, apart from the cold solidified mac & cheese, 😂... that looked pretty good (if a bit pricey though mate). But my biggest problem with a rack of ribs is, they're a lot of work to strip the meat off of the bone. The last ones i had, put me off them for good. It was mostly bone, with almost no meat, and plenty of rubbery connecting tissue. For the price of the ribs, i could have had a nice sized juicy steak. I'd have loved it, if you'd weighed the ribs before you started, then weighed the bones after. I bet if you'd got a couple of ounces of meat off them, that'd be pushing it. Haha. Anyway, well done mate. Cheers buddy.
